<TITLE> Nation marking Tagore's 66th death anniversary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 6 (bdnews24.com)  The nation is observing the 66th death anniversary of Rabindranath Tagore, The celebrated Bengali poet, novelist, painter, dramatist, short story writerthe myriad-minded cultural personality breathed his last on 22nd Shraban, 1348 Bangla year. He was born to the illustrious Tagore family iu Jorhashanko, Kolkata on 25th Boishakh, 1268 Bangla year. These two Bangla dates have so fondly been cherished in the hearts of the Bengalis that they are owned by even those who have not had the opportunity of accessing Tagore's works. Tagore's brilliance spread far and wide, transcending the Indian sub-continental bounds, illuminating many corners of the earth for over a century now. The national anthem of Bangladesh is again Tagore's immortal creation. He authored the India's national anthem too. Tagore was awarded the Nobel prize in literature in 1913 for his 'Geetanjali' collection of poems. A number of organisations including the cultural affairs ministry have drawn up daylong cultural programmes in observance of the day in Dhaka and across the country. Rabindra Sangeet Shilpi Sangsthha has undertaken a two-day programme starting Monday. Sponsored by Grameenphone, the programme titled 'Nishidin alokshikha joluk praney' will be inaugurated by its president famous Tagore song exponent Kalim Sharafi. The Indian High Commission has organised a Tagore song soiree at the National Museum at 7 pm. bd
